## AGENTS.md

Codex-cli automatically injects AGENTS.md files from `~/.codex` and every directory from repo root to the current working directory. The model is trained to closely follow these instructions.

- Files are pulled from `~/.codex` plus each directory from repo root to CWD.
- They're merged root-to-leaf order (global first, then deeper directories override).
- Each file appears as a separate user-role message: `# AGENTS.md instructions for <directory>`.

Use AGENTS.md to provide repo-specific conventions, tool preferences, and domain context without modifying the base system prompt.

