## Tools

### apply_patch (strongly recommended)
The model is trained on this exact diff format. Use the Responses API first-class tool or the freeform grammar implementation.

```python
# Responses API (preferred)
tools = [cast(ToolParam, {"type": "apply_patch"})]

# Freeform tool with context-free grammar
{
  "type": "custom",
  "name": "apply_patch_grammar",
  "description": "Use `apply_patch` to edit files. FREEFORM tool — do not wrap the patch in JSON.",
  "format": {"type": "grammar", "syntax": "lark", "definition": apply_patch_grammar}
}
```

### shell_command
Use `command` as a string (not a list) for best performance. Always set `workdir`. Avoid `cd` in the command string.

```json
{
  "type": "function",
  "name": "shell_command",
  "description": "Runs a shell command and returns its output. Always set workdir; avoid cd in the command string.",
  "parameters": {
    "type": "object",
    "properties": {
      "command": {"type": "string"},
      "workdir": {"type": "string"},
      "timeout_ms": {"type": "number"},
      "with_escalated_permissions": {"type": "boolean"},
      "justification": {"type": "string"}
    },
    "required": ["command"]
  }
}
```

